The font of the alt text in the placeholder box of images before they have been
downloaded should be made slightly smaller.

To do this we need a way of addressing the box itself, before the image has
been inserted, in CSS. Ideally, this would be a pseudo-*element* such as
  :-moz-placeholder
...and so we could add the following to ua.css:

   :-moz-placeholder {
      padding: 4px;
      font: smaller sans-serif;
      border: 1px inset;
   }

Ideally ideally, we should also have a pseudo-*class* to refer to the image when
the alt text is shown. This is covered by bug 11011.

The following code in buttonframe renderer is wrong for titledbuttons.

PRBool
nsButtonFrameRenderer::isDisabled()
{
  // get the content
  nsCOMPtr<nsIContent> content;
  mFrame->GetContent(getter_AddRefs(content));
  nsString value;
  if (NS_CONTENT_ATTR_HAS_VALUE == content->GetAttribute(mNameSpace,
nsHTMLAtoms::disabled, value))
    return PR_TRUE;

  return PR_FALSE;
}

It only checks to see if the attribute is present... this is correct for HTML
buttons, but incorrect for titled buttons... you need to actually see if the
value of the attribute is true for titled buttons, and only disable it if the
attribute is true (someone could specify a value of false for the disabled
attribute, for example).

Should take you 5 minutes to fix.

